From d98cd766f6051f6024930dfde370919deec758e6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:21:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] Upgrade wl_seat to version 5 and overhaul input handling

Clients like foot require wl_seat >= 5, which obligates the
compositor to terminate every pointer event group with a
wl_pointer.frame event and lets it announce key repeat parameters.

- wl_pointer: send frame events, axis_discrete for wheel detents,
  scale wheel deltas to sensible axis values, add the release
  handler, and implement set_cursor using NSCursor built from the
  committed cursor surface's buffer.
- wl_keyboard: send repeat_info to version 4+ clients and stop
  forwarding Cocoa autorepeat to them (they repeat themselves);
  replace the partial keycode table with a complete macOS to evdev
  translation (adapted from Wawona, MIT); send modifier keys as
  real key events derived from NSFlagsChanged, with modifier masks
  matching the shipped keymap (Shift, Control, Mod1=Option,
  Mod4=Command, Lock=Caps); send the mandatory modifiers event
  after keyboard enter; drop keys we cannot translate instead of
  sending keycode 0.
- wl_seat: handle get_touch (inert) and release so no request hits
  a NULL vtable slot.
- wl_surface: implement damage_buffer (mandatory in practice for
  wl_compositor version 4 clients); fire frame callbacks on
  damage-less and unmapping commits so clients waiting for a frame
  done event never deadlock; treat ARGB shm buffers as
  premultiplied, as the protocol specifies.
- Run the Wayland event loop source and client flushes in the
  common run loop modes so clients keep updating during native
  interactive window moves and resizes.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_0187CcHcrnoWzf7rzCaEDpR1
